features.name: IMS,IMS_C,IMS_HHH Poorly processive, error-prone DNA polymerase involved in untargeted mutagenesis. Copies undamaged DNA at stalled replication forks, which arise in vivo from mismatched or misaligned primer ends. These misaligned primers can be extended by PolIV. Exhibits no 3'-5' exonuclease (proofreading) activity. May be involved in translesional synthesis, in conjunction with the beta clamp from PolIII
TetR_N Bacterial regulatory proteins, tetR family
CTP_transf_like Reversibly transfers an adenylyl group from ATP to 4'- phosphopantetheine, yielding dephospho-CoA (dPCoA) and pyrophosphate

ACP_syn_III,ACP_syn_III_C Catalyzes the condensation reaction of fatty acid synthesis by the addition to an acyl acceptor of two carbons from malonyl-ACP. Catalyzes the first condensation reaction which initiates fatty acid synthesis and may therefore play a role in governing the total rate of fatty acid production. Possesses both acetoacetyl-ACP synthase and acetyl transacylase activities. Its substrate specificity determines the biosynthesis of branched- chain and or straight-chain of fatty acids

HGTP_anticodon,TGS,tRNA-synt_2b,tRNA_SAD Catalyzes the attachment of threonine to tRNA(Thr) in a two-step reaction L-threonine is first activated by ATP to form Thr-AMP and then transferred to the acceptor end of tRNA(Thr)
Sigma70_r2,Sigma70_r4_2 Belongs to the sigma-70 factor family. ECF subfamily
